cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the optimization of cache memory in GPGPUs, which is related to the architecture of the system. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The main focus of the paper is to improve the performance of GPGPUs, which falls under the performance sub-category. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): GPGPUs are widely used for parallel programming, and the paper discusses the optimization techniques for achieving high performance in parallel computing. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the programming concepts for GPGPUs and compares them with conventional programming concepts in CPUs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the best practices for achieving high performance in GPGPUs and identifies the suitability of CPU cache optimization techniques for GPGPUs, which falls under the software engineering sub-category.
